Swaziland Asked S. Africa to Help Prevent Revolt, S. Times Says

-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 
2011-04-03T12:16:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/swaziland-asked-s-africa-to-help-prevent-revolt-s-times-says.html
Swaziland’s King Mswati III asked
police in neighboring South African police to help monitor the
movements and communications of backers of domestic opposition
groups to prevent a Tunisia-style revolt against the monarchy,
the Sunday Times reported.  Swazi and South African officials had met, the
Johannesburg-based paper cited McIntosh Polela, the spokesman
for  South Africa ’s special crimes Hawks unit, as saying. Polela
didn’t know what the nature of the meeting was, it said.  -- Editors: Ana Monteiro, Shaji Mathew.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Franz Wild in Johannesburg at 
